cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the implementation of type classes in Haskell using Horn clauses and first-order resolution, which are topics related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses extensions to type class resolution, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) or formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper establishes incompleteness results for fragments of the proof system, which could be relevant to computational logic (cs.CL).
